To evaluate (A × B) ∪ {1}, we first need to find the Cartesian product A × B, which consists of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a ∈ A and b ∈ B.

A × B = {(1, 3), (2, 3)}

Now, we need to find the union of the set A × B and the set {1}. The union of two sets is the set of all elements that are in either of the sets.

(A × B) ∪ {1} = {(1, 3), (2, 3)} ∪ {1} = {(1, 3), (2, 3), 1}
